Lanark Community Club Website
Three-Prompt Copilot Plan for a Right-Sized Build
This document is a three-prompt build plan for using GitHub Copilot to stand up `lanarkcommunityclub.com` in a way that is practical, maintainable, secure, and appropriately scaled for a community club.
The framing assumes we are acting like a small internal Agile team doing a weekly community-involvement SWARM event: focused, collaborative, iterative, and disciplined enough to avoid overbuilding.
The goal is not to create the biggest possible platform. The goal is to create a durable community website with a modest member area that serves the Lanark Community Club well for years.
---
1. Product Framing
Product Vision
Create a trustworthy, welcoming, easy-to-maintain website for the Lanark Community Club (LCC) that supports:
public awareness
event visibility
donations
storytelling about local impact
scholarships and club history
a lightweight, private members area for internal coordination
Product Principles
Use these principles to guide every technical decision:
Do not overbuild
Prefer boring, proven technology
Make solo maintenance realistic
Keep public content easy to update
Keep member features intentionally constrained
Optimize for clarity over cleverness
Ship an MVP that the club can actually use
Use security best practices without enterprise theater
Design for mobile use and low-friction admin workflows
Let the technology serve the club, not the other way around
---
